# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Frontend build configuration
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# HOW TO USE:  copy this file to ".env" in the same folder, then edit the two
# values below to match YOUR setup.  These are read only at BUILD time
# (`npm run build`) and baked into the static files — so after changing them
# you must build again.
#
#     cp .env.example .env      # (Windows PowerShell:  Copy-Item .env.example .env)
#
# The ".env" file is git-ignored, so your values stay local to your machine.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# 1) VITE_API_BASE — the full HTTPS URL of the backend API (no trailing slash).
#    This is where the app sends login and chat requests. Point it at wherever
#    the FastAPI backend runs on your network.
#      - Same machine, behind a reverse proxy on the same domain? Leave it EMPTY
#        and serve the API under the same host (calls become same-origin).
#      - Backend on a different host/port? Set the absolute URL.
#    Examples:
#      VITE_API_BASE=https://copilot-api.nha.internal
#      VITE_API_BASE=https://10.20.30.40:8000
VITE_API_BASE=

# 2) VITE_BASE — the URL path the app is served from (keep the slashes exactly).
#      - Serving at the domain ROOT (https://copilot.nha.internal/)  -> use  /
#      - Serving under a SUBPATH   (https://portal.nha.internal/copilot/) -> use /copilot/
#    If you leave this empty, a production build defaults to /nha-copilot/
#    (the GitHub Pages layout), which will show a BLANK PAGE when hosted at a
#    root — so set it explicitly for self-hosting.
VITE_BASE=/
